Ten persons have been feared killed in Ondo State in an accident that occurred at Olu foam junction, along Ilesa/Akure/Owo highway, Akure, the State Capital. The ghastly accident involved a truck and an 18 seater bus. The truck with registration number KJA 14 XW was said to have collided with the bus from the opposite direction while avoiding a collision with an Okada rider. The trailer eventually crushed the Okada rider before colliding with the bus marked USL 498 XB. The bus was loaded with eighteen passengers including four underage children. The corpses of the victims have been deposited at UNIMED Teaching Hospital in Akure, the state capital.